# Memory Bank — Cursor Auto-Loader

> This `.mdc` file is a Cursor-specific wrapper. Its only job is to auto-inject
> the shared protocol and rules files into every Cursor session.
>
> The actual content lives in plain markdown files that any AI tool can read.

## Read These Files

1. **`memory-bank-protocol.md`** — Memory bank methodology, reading strategy, workflows, update protocol
2. **`project-rules.md`** — Project-specific rules, coding standards, constraints + dynamic sprint zone
3. **`memory-bank/INDEX.md`** — Routing hub, follow its reading strategy for the current task type

## Companion Rules

- **`.cursor/rules/update-memory-bank.mdc`** — Auto-updates memory bank after task completion
- **`.cursor/rules/create-memory-bank.mdc`** — Initializes memory bank for new projects
